<title>US and Other Evaluated Product Lists</title>

<H1>US and Other Evaluated Product Lists </H1>

The National Security Agency now makes the US Evaluated Products List
available on the World Wide Web at http://www.radium.ncsc.mil/tpep/:
<a href=http://www.radium.ncsc.mil/tpep/><br>NSA home page for the
Trusted Product Evaluation Program, including pointers to the
Evaluated Product List.</a>
<p>
In addition,
Germany has a list of their evaluated
   products (and also the UK ones) available at:<br>
   <a href=http://www.cci.de/cci/its/bsihaupt.htm>
   http://www.cci.de/cci/its/bsihaupt.htm</a>


<pre>
Abstract of US EPL showing all evaluations completed, in Formal Evaluation
Phase, or in Design Analysis Phase at level B1 and above as of 1 August 1994.
[SO IT IS NOW FAIRLY OLD:  SEE LINKS ABOVE FOR CURRENT INFORMATION]

Information based on Dockmaster EPL forum entries, including EPL listing
as published 4 Feb 94 and subsequent Product Evaluation Bulletins posted
in transactions through #371. 
 
Summary lines changed or added since summary of April 20 1993 start with '+'.
=========================================================================
