<Title>Formal Verification of Cryptographic Protocols</Title>

<h2>FORMAL VERIFICATION OF CRYPTOGRAPHIC PROTOCOLS</h2>

<HR>
<p>
This page is part of the web at the
<a href="http://www.itd.nrl.navy.mil/ITD/5540/">
 Center for High Assurance Computer Systems</a>.
<p>
<HR>

<H2>Objective</H2>

To develop and evaluate formal methods for the verification of
cryptographic protocols. One of our accomplishments is the NRL
Protocol Analyzer, a tool for the verification of security properties
of cryptographic protocols.
We also develop and use modal logics to analyze cryptographic protocols.

<P>
For a description of the NRL Protocol Analyzer, look
<a href="../publications/CHACS/1994meadows-pap.ps">
here</a>.


<H2>Researchers</H2>

<ul>
  <li> Catherine Meadows, Principal Investigator
  <li> Paul Syverson
</ul>

<a href="../publications/CHACS/CRYPTOindex.html">
 <H2>Publications</H2></a>


<HR>
<ADDRESS>
Formal Verification of Cryptographic Protocols / Catherine Meadows / meadows@itd.nrl.navy.mil
</ADDRESS>
Updated August 22, 1994

