<TITLE>What's New in Cipher</Title>
<H2>What's New in Cipher</H2>
<HR>
Since EI#19 was e-mailed December 23, 1996
<ul>
Nothing is new!
</ul>
Since EI#18 was e-mailed November 11, 1996
<ul>
<li> December 20-23: many things added and updated in preparation for new 
issue
<li> November 18: Added new note by Anderson and Kuhn to tamper papers
listed under that news-item.  Also added two new book reviews by
Bob Bruen, paperlist for ASIAN '96. 
</ul>
Since EI#17 was e-mailed October 1, 1996
<ul>
<li> November 8-11: updated many things, installed new news-items,
new letter from Editor, etc., in preparation for new issue.
<li> November 6 and 7: new Letter from the TC Chair, two book reviews
     by Bob Bruen, new LISTWATCH, etc.
<li> October 24 and after: more and notes on tamper attacks
<li> October 15: added DIMACS Workshop on Trust Management papers to
Reader's Guide.
<li> October 12: added pointer to new Anderson/Kuhn paper to New Reports
<li> October 10: added item on Javasoft forum to "Commentary and Opinion"
<li> October 9: added reports on ACM New Security Paradigms Workshop
and IFIP Working Conference and Multimedia Communications Security. Also
added paper list for NISSC '96 conference to Readers' Guide.
<li> October 7: installed and mailed final CFP for IEE S&P '97 conference.
</ul>
Since EI#16 was e-mailed July 28, 1996
<ul>
<li>29 September - 1 October: updated all areas and added news items 
<li>11 September, 1996: added new LISTWATCH column and report on 10th IFIP 
WG11.3 WC on Database Security.
</ul>
Since EI#15 was e-mailed June 1, 1996
<ul>
<li> 28 July, 1996: many items updated for issue release.
<li> 24 July, 1996: added many new items to journal papers part of Reader's Guide; many thanks to Anish Mathuria for these.
<li> 23 July, 1996: added several items, paper lists to Reader's Guide and
news item on E.O. 13010
<li> 16 July, 1996: added new letter from TC chair and updated officers list.
