<META NAME="resource-type" CONTENT="document">
<META NAME="distribution" CONTENT="global">
<LINK REL=STYLESHEET HREF="newrptrTL.css">
</HEAD>
<BODY LANG="EN">
 <A NAME="tex2html1092" HREF="node13.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC=".//next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html1090" HREF="node11.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC=".//up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html1086" HREF="node11.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC=".//previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html1094" HREF="node2.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC=".//contents_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html1095" HREF="node183.html"><IMG WIDTH=43 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="index" SRC=".//index_motif.gif"></A> <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html1093" HREF="node13.html">CSP: The Computational Framework</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html1091" HREF="node11.html">Solution Strategy</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html1087" HREF="node11.html">Solution Strategy</A>
<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION02121000000000000000">Overview of Tools Used</A></H2>
<P>
<A NAME="OverviewofToolsUsed">&#160;</A>
<P>
The question arises why we use both interactive proof and model
checking technology to construct the repeater argument.  The use of
interactive mathematical proof as a means of gaining assurance that an
implementation conforms to its critical requirements is a (human)
labor intensive process.  Model checking can provide a comparable
level of assurance for portions of a system verification at a
substantial savings in time and human labor.  Unfortunately, model
checking currently applies only to the verification of relatively
low-level requirements.  FDR, for example, is used to verify that an
implementation conforms to a CSP process specification.  We need the
EVES interactive prover to verify that the CSP process specification
conforms to a more intuitive statement of the critical
requirements.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html1096" HREF="node13.html#SECTION02121100000000000000">CSP: The Computational Framework</A>
