<BR> <P>
<H1><A NAME="SECTION02220000000000000000">EVES Notation</A></H1>
<P>
<A NAME="EVESNotation">&#160;</A>
<P>
We use SVerdi to write definitions, conjectures, and
proofs.  These entities can be organized using the built-in library
mechanism.  This mechanism provides a foundation from which to encode
the CSP Traces Refinement model in EVES, to specify CSP applications and to
prove that they satisfy their critical (trace) requirements.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html1203" HREF="node21.html#SECTION02221000000000000000">Non-Executable Definitions</A>
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html1204" HREF="node22.html#SECTION02222000000000000000">Executable Definitions</A>
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html1205" HREF="node23.html#SECTION02223000000000000000">Conjectures</A>
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html1206" HREF="node24.html#SECTION02224000000000000000">Proof Commands</A>
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html1207" HREF="node25.html#SECTION02225000000000000000">Library Mechanism</A>
</UL>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Andy Moore <BR>
Tue Aug 20 13:26:31 EDT 1996</I>
