<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html2246" HREF="node94.html">Proof Structure of Inchar</A>
<BR> <P>
<H1><A NAME="SECTION03300000000000000000">Put Component Refinement</A></H1>
<P>
<A NAME="PutComponentRefinement">&#160;</A>
<P>
This chapter uses the same procedural approach to the design of
<TT>Put</TT> as used in the last chapter in the design of <TT>Get</TT> (see the
introduction to Chapter&nbsp;<A HREF="node78.html#GetComponentRefinement">6</A> for a
description of the approach).  We begin in Section&nbsp;<A HREF="node96.html#OverviewofthePutDesign">7.1</A> by describing an overview of the design of <TT>Put</TT> in
CSP.  Section&nbsp;<A HREF="node97.html#FormalSpecificationofthePutDesign">7.2</A> recasts
this design in SVerdi by modeling CSP processes as SVerdi procedures
and CSP operations as SVerdi statements.  Critical requirements Assert 7.2L
and Assert 8.2L are cast as a post condition on the procedure representing
<TT>Put</TT>.  Finally Section&nbsp;<A HREF="node98.html#JustificationofthePutDesign">7.3</A>
decomposes these requirements onto the primary procedures of the
design and argues that the design satisfies the set of critical
requirements of <TT>Put</TT>.
<P>
