<H2><A NAME="SECTION05121000000000000000">Definition of has_char</A></H2>
<P>
<TT>has_char</TT> determines whether a bit sequence begins with a valid
delimited character.  It does this by asking whether there is some
character that when delimited by a <TT>startbit</TT>/<TT>stopbit</TT> forms a
prefix of the bit sequence.
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="maclab129">&#160;</A>
<B>&lt;</B><I>Definition of has_char</I><B>&gt;</B><B>[</B>129<B>]</B><A NAME=11911>&#160;</A><B>=</B> <BR><TT>&nbsp;</TT> <TT>&nbsp;&nbsp;function&nbsp;has_char&nbsp;(s,&nbsp;chsz)&nbsp;=<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;begin<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;some&nbsp;c:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;is_char&nbsp;(c,&nbsp;chsz)<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;and&nbsp;startbit&nbsp;]-&nbsp;(c&nbsp;&nbsp;.&lt;stopbit&gt;.)&nbsp;.&lt;=.&nbsp;s<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;end&nbsp;has_char;</TT>
<P>
This macro is invoked in definition <A HREF="node172.html#maclab201">201</A>.<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<BR> <HR>
