<BODY LANG="EN">
 <A NAME="tex2html2998" HREF="node148.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC=".//next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html2996" HREF="node143.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC=".//up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html2992" HREF="node146.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC=".//previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html3000" HREF="node2.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC=".//contents_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html3001" HREF="node183.html"><IMG WIDTH=43 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="index" SRC=".//index_motif.gif"></A> <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html2999" HREF="node148.html">Set of even parity </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html2997" HREF="node143.html">Secondary Operations</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html2993" HREF="node146.html">Definition of char_head</A>
<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION05124000000000000000">Definition of char_tail</A></H2>
<P>
<TT>char_tail</TT> returns all but the first character of a bit
sequence (including delimiters) independent of the first character's
validity.
<TT>char_tail (s, chsz)</TT> removes the first
<TT>chsz + 2</TT> bits of the bit sequence <TT>s</TT>.  By default, we delete
only two bits (the bits representing the delimiters) for all
values of <TT>chsz</TT> less than 0.
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="maclab132">&#160;</A>
<B>&lt;</B><I>Definition of char_tail</I><B>&gt;</B><B>[</B>132<B>]</B><A NAME=11961>&#160;</A><B>=</B> <BR><TT>&nbsp;</TT> <TT>&nbsp;&nbsp;function&nbsp;char_tail&nbsp;(s,&nbsp;chsz)&nbsp;=<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;begin<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if&nbsp;chsz&nbsp;&gt;=&nbsp;0<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;then&nbsp;tr!remove_first_n&nbsp;(s,&nbsp;chsz&nbsp;+&nbsp;2)<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;else&nbsp;tr!remove_first_n&nbsp;(s,&nbsp;2)&nbsp;end&nbsp;if<BR>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;end&nbsp;char_tail;</TT>
<P>
This macro is invoked in definition <A HREF="node172.html#maclab201">201</A>.<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<BR> <HR>
