<P>
<P>
<P>
<TT>mach</TT> provides facilities to send and receive characters very
similar to those provided to send and receive bits.  The primary
difference is that, on reception, the character size <TT>chsz</TT> is
passed and the predicate <TT>cseq!is_char</TT> is guaranteed to hold for
the character received.
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="maclab174">&#160;</A>
